          <int-org-section id="IO-UN.1025" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Commission</heading>
               <p>The Commission normally meets every two years at ministerial level. It considers matters relating to the economic and social development of the region, reviews activities of the organization, and adopts programmes of work. The 40th session was scheduled to be hosted by Peru, in October 2024. Member states may gather between Commission meetings in ECLAC’s Committee of the Whole. The Commission has established the following ad hoc and permanent subsidiary bodies:</p>
               <gen-list>
                    <item>Caribbean Development and Co-operation Committee</item>
                    <item>Committee of the Whole</item>
                    <item>Conference on Science, Innovation and Information and Communications Technologies</item>
                    <item>Regional Conference on Population and Development</item>
                    <item>Regional Conference on Social Development</item>
                    <item>Regional Conference on South-South Cooperation</item>
                    <item>Regional Conference on Women</item>
                    <item>Regional Council for Planning</item>
                    <item>Statistical Conference of the Americas</item>
               </gen-list>
          </int-org-section>
          <int-org-section id="IO-UN.1033" sllink="SLSDOC" slsdocrf="INT-ORG-SECTREF">
               <heading>Secretariat</heading>
               <p>The secretariat is headed by the Offices of the Executive Secretary and of the Secretary of the Commission. ECLAC's work programme is carried out by the following divisions: Economic Development; Social Development; Economic and Social Planning (ILPES); Gender Affairs; International Trade and Integration; Natural Resources; Population (CELADE); Statistics; Sustainable Development and Human Settlements; Production, Productivity and Management; Programme Planning and Operations; and Publications and Web Services.</p>
